docs.abstract: Officials might weaken a law that bans chokeholds and other police maneuvers that restrict airflow.
docs.snippet: Officials might weaken a law that bans chokeholds and other police maneuvers that restrict airflow.
docs.lead_paragraph: In June, as New York City was gripped by protests over the death of George Floyd, the City Council passed legislation banning police officers from using maneuvers that restrict a person’s airflow. Now the Council, cowed by pressure from police unions and officials, is considering rolling back part of this important step toward police accountability.

headline.main: New York City Council, Don’t Roll Back Police Reforms
headline.print_headline: Hands Off New York’s Police Reforms

docs.abstract: How to end the racial disparity in vehicle stops.
docs.snippet: How to end the racial disparity in vehicle stops.
docs.lead_paragraph: In his speech last week in Pittsburgh, Joe Biden pushed back against Donald Trump’s mischaracterization of him as soft on crime and beholden to progressives intent on defunding or abolishing police departments. He pledged to work with mayors and governors to tamp down violence. He also vowed to make progress on police reform, invoking the names of Breonna Taylor, George Floyd and Jacob Blake, and the cause of racial justice for which they have come to stand.

headline.main: It Is Possible to Reform the Police
headline.print_headline: Still Guilty of Driving While Black

docs.abstract: Some demonstrators in New York have taken on informal but crucial roles over a summer of marches. Here’s how to spot them.
docs.snippet: Some demonstrators in New York have taken on informal but crucial roles over a summer of marches. Here’s how to spot them.
docs.lead_paragraph: Only a few weeks after the first of what would become near-daily Black Lives Matter protests in New York City, Justina Heckard found herself on her bicycle in Brooklyn, leading a march in loose formation with other cyclists. An altercation with a driver left a protester injured, and Ms. Heckard and her fellow demonstrators decided they would need to sharpen their tactics.

headline.main: From Bike Blockers to Street Medics: The Anatomy of an N.Y.C. Protest
